HB 202 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session McMakin
Abstract: Requires salary information to be included within a job announcement for a
vacant classified state civil service position and provides for a notice of rejection or
a notice that the vacancy has been filled to be sent to applicants.
Proposed law requires the Dept. of State Civil Service to list the salary or salary range of a
vacant classified position within the job announcement.
Proposed law provides that if an individual applies for a vacant classified position posted by
the Dept. of State Civil Service and the individual is rejected or the vacancy has been filled,
the Dept. is required to notify the individual of the rejection or that the vacancy has been
filled.
(Adds R.S. 42:375.1)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on House and
Governmental Affairs to the original bill:
1. Provide that proposed law applies to classified positions instead of unclassified
positions.
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Require the Department of State Civil Service to notify an applicant when the
position the applicant applied for has been filled.
